  "prompt": "What happens when you withdraw linkedin invitation?",
  "response": "When you withdraw a LinkedIn invitation, the following happens:\n\n*   **The recipient is notified:** The pending invitation disappears from their \"My Network\" page. They will no longer be able to accept the invitation.\n*   **You are removed from their \"People You May Know\" list:** LinkedIn's algorithm typically stops suggesting you to them as a potential connection.\n*   **They are not notified of the withdrawal:** LinkedIn does not send the recipient a specific notification that you withdrew the invitation. They will simply notice the invitation is no longer there.\n*   **You can resend an invitation (with a caveat):** You can resend an invitation, but there's a limit. LinkedIn might prevent you from resending an invitation to the same person if they've ignored or declined your invitation several times. There might be a waiting period.\n*   **It's generally considered less awkward than a rejection:** Withdrawing an invitation is often seen as less harsh than having the recipient reject it.\n*   **No impact on existing connections:** If you are already connected to the person, withdrawing an invitation has no effect on your existing connection. It only impacts pending invitations.",
